259
00:20:43,856 --> 00:20:45,824
Lewis, this is Harry Anders,

260
00:20:45,858 --> 00:20:47,758
owner of the best
jazz club in London.

261
00:20:47,793 --> 00:20:49,818
l heard all about you, Harry.

262
00:20:49,862 --> 00:20:54,629
ln my college days l used to play
a little jazz myself-- soprano sax.

263
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:57,431
Bechet.
Sidney Bechet, he was my hero.

264
00:20:57,469 --> 00:20:59,994
Best soprano sax
player ever.

265
00:21:00,039 --> 00:21:02,769
Harry, this is Lewis Mansdorf,
my husband.

266
00:21:02,808 --> 00:21:04,639
Oh.

267
00:21:04,677 --> 00:21:06,611
We seem to have
the same tastes, Harry.

268
00:21:06,645 --> 00:21:08,875
Like minds, eh?

269
00:21:08,914 --> 00:21:10,711
Great to meet you.

270
00:21:10,749 --> 00:21:13,047
Now l gotta go and do
some gripping and greeting.

271
00:21:13,085 --> 00:21:15,053
Please excuse me.

272
00:21:22,061 --> 00:21:25,030
