283
00:21:49,855 --> 00:21:52,756
That gloopy look.

284
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:54,850
Don't go soft on me, please.

285
00:21:56,595 --> 00:21:58,085
Now what the hell
is ''gloopy''?

286
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:01,759
You don't fool me.
l know men like you, remember?

287
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,768
All that tough-guy talk,

288
00:22:03,802 --> 00:22:06,236
and scar tissue
on the outside,

289
00:22:06,271 --> 00:22:08,398
and hopeless romantics
on the inside.

290
00:22:09,608 --> 00:22:11,576
Well...

291
00:22:11,610 --> 00:22:15,410
it's nice to know that you have
such a high opinion of me.

292
00:22:15,447 --> 00:22:17,415
lt isn't that.

293
00:22:17,449 --> 00:22:20,475
This has to be
strictly temporary, okay?

294
00:22:20,519 --> 00:22:23,249
Mm-hm.

295
00:22:23,288 --> 00:22:25,722
Strictly Temporary
is my middle name.

296
00:22:33,432 --> 00:22:36,128
Lovely steak today!
l've got some lovely steak!

297
00:22:36,168 --> 00:22:37,795
Good morning, Harry.

298
00:22:37,836 --> 00:22:39,804
Harry, l want to
ask you something.

299
00:22:39,838 --> 00:22:43,740
l have a problem, l think, but l don't
know if l should involve you.

300
00:22:43,776 --> 00:22:46,540
How fresh?

301
00:22:46,578 --> 00:22:48,546
Today's catch, Harry.

302
00:22:48,580 --> 00:22:50,775
You wouldn't try
to con me, would you, Marvin?

303
00:22:50,816 --> 00:22:52,943
This sea-bass died
of old age.

304
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:57,884
- Are you in trouble, Stacy?
- Maybe.

305
00:22:57,923 --> 00:22:59,891
Trouble is
my middle name.

306
00:22:59,925 --> 00:23:02,917
l thought ''strictly temporary''
was your middle name.

307
00:23:02,961 --> 00:23:05,589
ln England, we're very big
on middle names.

308
00:23:05,631 --> 00:23:07,258
Tell me what
your problem is.

309
00:23:07,299 --> 00:23:11,099
When Lewis and l came here,
l had an affair with an American.

310
00:23:11,136 --> 00:23:14,628
He took the relationship
much more seriously than l did.

311
00:23:14,673 --> 00:23:16,971
He started writing
these crazy letters, and--

312
00:23:17,009 --> 00:23:19,204
l'm afraid the tabloids
might get ahold of one

313
00:23:19,244 --> 00:23:21,576
and make it really
difficult for Lewis.

314
00:23:21,613 --> 00:23:23,979
You want me to find this guy
and have a chat with him?

315
00:23:24,016 --> 00:23:26,541
Well, no. l want you to find him
so l can talk with him.

316
00:23:28,921 --> 00:23:32,618
You know, my fee
may be beyond your means.

317
00:23:35,127 --> 00:23:37,425
l'm a very wealthy woman,
Mr. Anders.

318
00:23:37,463 --> 00:23:39,829
l'm still gonna require
a down payment.

319
00:24:09,428 --> 00:24:11,726
l drew a blank
with the lmmigration people.

320
00:24:11,764 --> 00:24:14,790
Nobody of that name through
Passport Control in the past six weeks.

321
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:19,270
l checked the Special Branch
watch list. Nothing doing there either.

322
00:24:19,304 --> 00:24:22,831
You and l should have
a word with the Yanks.

323
00:24:22,875 --> 00:24:25,309
l know some of their
security people at the Embassy.

324
00:24:25,344 --> 00:24:27,312
l don't think so, Ozzie.

325
00:24:27,346 --> 00:24:29,473
This has got to be handled
with some finesse.

326
00:24:29,515 --> 00:24:32,245
And finesse is not
one of their strong points.

327
00:24:32,284 --> 00:24:35,276
Well, l do have an in
with a Fraud Squad guy

328
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:37,948
