333
00:24:51,003 --> 00:24:53,972
Well, he's got to pay off
computer people.

334
00:24:54,006 --> 00:24:56,873
lt's highly not legal.

335
00:24:56,909 --> 00:24:59,605
What's the commission
on your favors these days, Ozzie?

336
00:24:59,645 --> 00:25:02,409
- Eh?
- Still 30%, is it?

337
00:25:02,447 --> 00:25:04,415
Or have you
pushed it up to 50?

338
00:25:04,449 --> 00:25:06,417
l wouldn't cheat you, Harry.

339
00:25:06,451 --> 00:25:08,419
l hate taking your money.

340
00:25:08,453 --> 00:25:10,114
l know, Ozzie.

341
00:25:10,155 --> 00:25:12,123
You're a good old pal.

342
00:25:18,163 --> 00:25:20,757
Oy! Oy!
Busted. Come here!

343
00:25:20,799 --> 00:25:24,098
Harry, we got him.
We got the tea leaf.

344
00:25:24,136 --> 00:25:26,195
Bastard!
Come here!

345
00:25:26,238 --> 00:25:29,503
Watch your backs.
Stand away, luv.

346
00:25:34,313 --> 00:25:36,781
Oy, you!

347
00:25:36,815 --> 00:25:39,613
Don't be alarmed, that's just
part of the entertainment.

348
00:25:45,858 --> 00:25:47,655
lt's a mistake!

349
00:25:47,693 --> 00:25:50,287
lt's not what you think, Harry.
Honest it ain't.

350
00:25:50,329 --> 00:25:53,492
What do you prefer, Westy,
playing cards or playing football?

351
00:25:53,532 --> 00:25:55,693
lf it's cards,
l'm gonna break your leg,

352
00:25:55,734 --> 00:25:58,430
if it's football,
l'm gonna break your arm.

353
00:25:58,470 --> 00:26:00,734
- Leg or arm?
- Harry?

354
00:26:00,772 --> 00:26:02,672
- What?
- l got the old Bill on the phone.

355
00:26:02,708 --> 00:26:05,074
- Tell him to wait.
- The bloke says it's urgent.

356
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:06,907
Name of Osgood.

357
00:26:08,714 --> 00:26:10,409
This is your lucky day,
Westy.

358
00:26:10,449 --> 00:26:12,417
Let him go.

359
00:26:23,662 --> 00:26:27,860
- Are you sure it's him?
- Close it comes as will be.

360
00:26:27,900 --> 00:26:30,926
lt's the Villa Venetia,
Critchley line.

361
00:26:30,969 --> 00:26:32,937
Southeast London.

362
00:26:32,971 --> 00:26:34,939
He likes it here.

363
00:26:34,973 --> 00:26:37,771
He's used his card four times
in the past 10 days.

364
00:26:37,809 --> 00:26:39,777
The maitre d'
eyeballed him for me.

365
00:26:39,811 --> 00:26:42,279
Stay on him.
l'll be there in 20 minutes.

366
00:26:51,323 --> 00:26:53,883
- Hello?
- Write this down.

367
00:26:53,926 --> 00:26:55,894
The Critchley Hotel,

368
00:26:55,928 --> 00:26:58,988
station approach,
Southeast London.

369
00:26:59,031 --> 00:27:00,999
- Near London Bridge.
- You found him.

370
00:27:01,033 --> 00:27:03,194
Write it down, Stacy.

371
00:27:03,235 --> 00:27:06,068
''Critchley Hotel,

372
00:27:06,104 --> 00:27:08,698
station approach, near...

373
00:27:08,740 --> 00:27:10,708
London Bridge.''

374
00:27:10,742 --> 00:27:13,506
What do you
want me to do?

375
00:27:13,545 --> 00:27:15,672
Just make sure
he doesn't leave.

376
00:27:15,714 --> 00:27:17,477
l'll be there as soon as l can.

377
00:27:31,863 --> 00:27:33,831
Hello, Ozzie.

378
00:27:33,865 --> 00:27:36,390
Christ, Harry.
l never saw you coming.

379
00:27:36,435 --> 00:27:38,403
You must have been
a good spook in your day.

380
00:27:38,437 --> 00:27:40,405
James bloody Bond, mate.

381
00:27:40,439 --> 00:27:42,304
Which one is he?

382
00:27:42,341 --> 00:27:45,469
That's him-- good-looking kid
sitting on his own there.

383
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:48,035
There's gonna be
no rough stuff, is there, Harry?

384
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:50,173
l did this as a favor,
you know, off-duty.

385
00:27:50,215 --> 00:27:52,445
You did this
for the 300 quid, Ozzie,

386
00:27:52,484 --> 00:27:54,714
so don't give me
the Good Samaritan stuff.

387
00:28:03,829 --> 00:28:06,161
That's the sort of place
where defrocked vicars

388
00:28:06,198 --> 00:28:08,792
take young boys
and hang themselves after.

389
00:28:12,671 --> 00:28:16,129
Keep an eye on him, Ozzie.
l wanna make a phone call.

390
00:28:56,181 --> 00:28:57,808
Ozzie?

391
00:28:57,849 --> 00:29:00,147
Ozzie!

392
00:29:49,734 --> 00:29:51,429
Shit.

393
00:30:20,632 --> 00:30:21,963
Osgood?

394
00:30:27,639 --> 00:30:29,664
Osgood!

395
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:43,551
Jesus Christ!

396
00:31:27,432 --> 00:31:29,423
Come on!

397
00:31:37,776 --> 00:31:39,835
Fuck.

398
00:31:39,878 --> 00:31:42,472
Critchley Hotel.

399
00:31:59,297 --> 00:32:01,265
Want some milk
in that, mate?

400
00:32:01,299 --> 00:32:02,994
A lot of milk.

401
00:32:06,404 --> 00:32:08,167
Cheers.

402
00:32:11,443 --> 00:32:14,571
You are in a world
of trouble, my friend.

403
00:32:14,613 --> 00:32:17,081
l haven't done anything.

404
00:32:17,115 --> 00:32:19,447
l've told you,
Ozzie was an old pal.

405
00:32:19,484 --> 00:32:21,679
lf l thought--

406
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:24,951
l don't know who the American guy was. l
know nothing about him.

407
00:32:24,990 --> 00:32:26,958
- So who does?
- l wanna help you--

408
00:32:26,992 --> 00:32:30,428
You'd better had, friend, or you're
gonna get a smack in the gums.

409
00:32:30,462 --> 00:32:32,657
Ozzie was a cop.
He was one of us.

410
00:32:32,697 --> 00:32:34,665
No offense, fellas...

411
00:32:34,699 --> 00:32:36,997
but l'd feel a lot
more comfortable

412
00:32:37,035 --> 00:32:39,230
talking about this
at a higher level.

413
00:32:39,271 --> 00:32:40,795
Nothing personal.

414
00:32:40,839 --> 00:32:43,239
l don't smoke,

415
00:32:43,275 --> 00:32:45,004
l don't drink,

416
00:32:45,043 --> 00:32:47,568
l don't particularly
like women.

417
00:32:47,612 --> 00:32:49,375
My primary pleasure

418
00:32:49,414 --> 00:32:52,679
is writing my name on people's foreheads
with a baseball bat.

419
00:33:05,797 --> 00:33:07,765
Let's go through
this again, Anders.

420
00:33:07,799 --> 00:33:09,767
Who were you
working for?

421
00:33:09,801 --> 00:33:12,929
For the last time,
l wasn't working for anybody.

422
00:33:12,971 --> 00:33:14,461
l was doing a favor
for a lady.

423
00:33:14,506 --> 00:33:16,531
Oh, yeah-- the wife
of the American Ambassador.

424
00:33:16,574 --> 00:33:18,804
And if l thought she had
anything to do with it--

425
00:33:18,843 --> 00:33:20,834
You'd do what?
Kill her too?

426
00:33:20,879 --> 00:33:23,746
- l didn't kill anyone.
- You're lying.

427
00:33:23,782 --> 00:33:25,272
l am telling you the truth.

428
00:33:25,317 --> 00:33:28,343
How come when we checked
with the American Embassy, they said

429
00:33:28,386 --> 00:33:31,822
they'd never heard of you, and told us
the American Ambassador's wife

430
00:33:31,856 --> 00:33:35,053
had been in Paris
since yesterday evening?

431
00:33:35,093 --> 00:33:37,857
- They're lying.
- Oh, they're lying.

432
00:33:37,896 --> 00:33:40,091
- The American Embassy is lying?
- Mm-hm.

433
00:33:40,131 --> 00:33:42,861
Not the crooked cheapskate
club owner who's found

434
00:33:42,901 --> 00:33:46,860
with the copper's blood
all over his hands. Oh, no.

435
00:33:46,905 --> 00:33:49,601
