and come home in a wooden box.

489
00:39:49,333 --> 00:39:51,358
Go and have a cup of tea.

490
00:39:55,039 --> 00:39:58,099
Thank God the world
is full of bad guys, eh, Harry?

491
00:39:58,142 --> 00:40:00,110
l'd never pay the rent
if they weren't.

492
00:40:00,144 --> 00:40:02,112
Hello, Garcia.
How are you?

493
00:40:02,146 --> 00:40:03,773
l'm all right. And you?

494
00:40:03,815 --> 00:40:05,783
Yeah, l'm fine.

495
00:40:05,817 --> 00:40:08,285
Maybe l went into the wrong business
when l came out.

496
00:40:08,319 --> 00:40:10,116
Yeah, you wanna swap?

497
00:40:10,154 --> 00:40:11,985
l'll have a nightclub any day.

498
00:40:12,023 --> 00:40:15,083
You try teaching nervous businessmen to
be Machine Gun Kelly.

499
00:40:18,096 --> 00:40:22,032
The hardest thing is teaching them
the killer instinct.

500
00:40:22,066 --> 00:40:24,034
l had a problem with that.

501
00:40:24,068 --> 00:40:26,798
You? Leave off!

502
00:40:26,838 --> 00:40:30,069
You were one of the rare ones--
always had it, you were born with it.

503
00:40:30,108 --> 00:40:32,076
Maybe, maybe not.

504
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:35,273
- Have you got five minutes?
- Yeah. Here, come in here.

505
00:40:39,684 --> 00:40:41,982
He wired an alarm system
into his hotel room

506
00:40:42,019 --> 00:40:43,953
so he wouldn't
be taken by surprise.

